			matters&apos; (matters not arbitrable) and decisions of the Railway
			<lb />
			authorities thereon will be final and binding.
			<lb />
			45. Clause 63 has further been cemented by use of the
			<lb />
			expression &quot;provided further that &apos;excepted matters&apos; shall stand
			<lb />
			specifically excluded from the purview of the Arbitration clause.&quot;
			<lb />
			46. A further look at clause 64.(1) of the Standard General
			<lb />
			Conditions shows that apart from the &apos;excepted matters&apos; referred
			<lb />
			to in clause 63 of the Conditions, all disputes are liable to be
