			<lb />
			49. In the extant factual matrix, since the contract had been
			<lb />
			rescinded while invoking clause 62.(1)(vii) of the General Terms
			<lb />
			and Conditions, the arbitration clause namely clause 63 has been
			<lb />
			rendered innately and intrinsically redundant -like a vestigial
			<lb />
			organ in the human body -which exists but is non-functional … …
			<lb />
			50. As an upshot of the discussion aforesaid, this Court is of the
			<lb />
			considered view that the applicant does not even have an
